            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EWe%20can%20almost%20always%20trace%20our%20successes%20and%20failures%20to%20our%20seeking%20of%20God.%20When%20we%20are%20humble%20and%20childlike%2C%20we%20sense%20our%20total%20dependence%20upon%20and%20hunger%20for%20God.%20Prayer%20becomes%20easy%20and%20natural%20because%20we%20are%20so%20dependent.%20When%20we%20become%20proud%20and%20self-sufficient%2C%20however%2C%20we%20stop%20praying%20and%20start%20acting.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20Lord%20helped%20Uzziah%20%22wonderfully%20until%20he%20became%20very%20powerful.%20But%20when%20he%20had%20become%20powerful%2C%20he%20also%20became%20proud%2C%20which%20led%20to%20his%20downfall.%20.%20.%20.%22%20(2%20Chronicles%2026%3A15-16).%20Satan%20trapped%20Uzziah%20in%20the%20same%20snare%20that%20he%20himself%20had%20fallen%20into%20in%20eternity%20past.%20Pride%20had%20caused%20Satan%20to%20be%20cast%20out%20of%20heaven%2C%20and%20pride%20caused%20Uzziah%20to%20be%20cast%20out%20of%20the%20temple.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20his%20arrogant%20attitude%20and%20defiant%20spirit%20toward%20the%20priests%20of%20God%2C%20Uzziah%20developed%20terminal%20leprosy.%20If%20only%20he%20had%20remained%20childlike%2C%20humble%2C%20and%20dependent!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EOur%20prayer%20lives%20reveal%20our%20heart%20attitudes.%20Therefore%2C%20we%20need%20to%20keep%20seeking%20the%20Lord%2C%20even%20if%20our%20minds%20tell%20us%20we%20have%20%22made%20it.%22%20God%20may%20be%20checking%20out%20our%20dependence%20attitudes!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "2Chr.26:1-28:27",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E2%20Chronicles%2026%3A1-28%3A27%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E26%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EUzziah%20Rules%20in%20Judah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EAll%20the%20people%20of%20Judah%20had%20crowned%20Amaziah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sixteen-year-old%20son%2C%20Uzziah%2C%20as%20king%20in%20place%20of%20his%20father.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EAfter%20his%20father%26%23x2019%3Bs%20death%2C%20Uzziah%20rebuilt%20the%20town%20of%20Elath%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E26%3A2%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%20version%20(see%20also%202%26%23xA0%3BKgs%2014%3A22%3B%2016%3A6)%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EEloth%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Elath.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20restored%20it%20to%20Judah.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EUzziah%20was%20sixteen%20years%20old%20when%20he%20became%20king%2C%20and%20he%20reigned%20in%20Jerusalem%20fifty-two%20years.%20His%20mother%20was%20Jecoliah%20from%20Jerusalem.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20did%20what%20was%20pleasing%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sight%2C%20just%20as%20his%20father%2C%20Amaziah%2C%20had%20done.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EUzziah%20sought%20God%20during%20the%20days%20of%20Zechariah%2C%20who%20taught%20him%20to%20fear%20God.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E26%3A5%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Syriac%20and%20Greek%20versions%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3Ewho%20instructed%20him%20in%20divine%20visions.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20And%20as%20long%20as%20the%20king%20sought%20guidance%20from%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20God%20gave%20him%20success.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EUzziah%20declared%20war%20on%20the%20Philistines%20and%20broke%20down%20the%20walls%20of%20Gath%2C%20Jabneh%2C%20and%20Ashdod.%20Then%20he%20built%20new%20towns%20in%20the%20Ashdod%20area%20and%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20Philistia.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EGod%20helped%20him%20in%20his%20wars%20against%20the%20Philistines%2C%20his%20battles%20with%20the%20Arabs%20of%20Gur%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E26%3A7%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%20version%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EGur-baal.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20his%20wars%20with%20the%20Meunites.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20Meunites%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E26%3A8%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%20version%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EAmmonites.%3C%2Fem%3E%20Compare%2026%3A7.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20paid%20annual%20tribute%20to%20him%2C%20and%20his%20fame%20spread%20even%20to%20Egypt%2C%20for%20he%20had%20become%20very%20powerful.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_9%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EUzziah%20built%20fortified%20towers%20in%20Jerusalem%20at%20the%20Corner%20Gate%2C%20at%20the%20Valley%20Gate%2C%20and%20at%20the%20angle%20in%20the%20wall.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_10%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20also%20constructed%20forts%20in%20the%20wilderness%20and%20dug%20many%20water%20cisterns%2C%20because%20he%20kept%20great%20herds%20of%20livestock%20in%20the%20foothills%20of%20Judah%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E26%3A10%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20Shephelah.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20on%20the%20plains.%20He%20was%20also%20a%20man%20who%20loved%20the%20soil.%20He%20had%20many%20workers%20who%20cared%20for%20his%20farms%20and%20vineyards%2C%20both%20on%20the%20hillsides%20and%20in%20the%20fertile%20valleys.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_11%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EUzziah%20had%20an%20army%20of%20well-trained%20warriors%2C%20ready%20to%20march%20into%20battle%2C%20unit%20by%20unit.%20This%20army%20had%20been%20mustered%20and%20organized%20by%20Jeiel%2C%20the%20secretary%20of%20the%20army%2C%20and%20his%20assistant%2C%20Maaseiah.%20They%20were%20under%20the%20direction%20of%20Hananiah%2C%20one%20of%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20officials.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_12%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EThese%20regiments%20of%20mighty%20warriors%20were%20commanded%20by%202%2C600%20clan%20leaders.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_13%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20army%20consisted%20of%20307%2C500%20men%2C%20all%20elite%20troops.%20They%20were%20prepared%20to%20assist%20the%20king%20against%20any%20enemy.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_14%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EUzziah%20provided%20the%20entire%20army%20with%20shields%2C%20spears%2C%20helmets%2C%20coats%20of%20mail%2C%20bows%2C%20and%20sling%20stones.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_15%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20he%20built%20structures%20on%20the%20walls%20of%20Jerusalem%2C%20designed%20by%20experts%20to%20protect%20those%20who%20shot%20arrows%20and%20hurled%20large%20stones%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E26%3A15%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Eto%20shoot%20arrows%20and%20hurl%20large%20stones.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20from%20the%20towers%20and%20the%20corners%20of%20the%20wall.%20His%20fame%20spread%20far%20and%20wide%2C%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20gave%20him%20marvelous%20help%2C%20and%20he%20became%20very%20powerful.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_16%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EUzziah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Sin%20and%20Punishment%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20when%20he%20had%20become%20powerful%2C%20he%20also%20became%20proud%2C%20which%20led%20to%20his%20downfall.%20He%20sinned%20against%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20his%20God%20by%20entering%20the%20sanctuary%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple%20and%20personally%20burning%20incense%20on%20the%20incense%20altar.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_17%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EAzariah%20the%20high%20priest%20went%20in%20after%20him%20with%20eighty%20other%20priests%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20all%20brave%20men.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_18%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20confronted%20King%20Uzziah%20and%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BIt%20is%20not%20for%20you%2C%20Uzziah%2C%20to%20burn%20incense%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20That%20is%20the%20work%20of%20the%20priests%20alone%2C%20the%20descendants%20of%20Aaron%20who%20are%20set%20apart%20for%20this%20work.%20Get%20out%20of%20the%20sanctuary%2C%20for%20you%20have%20sinned.%20The%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20God%20will%20not%20honor%20you%20for%20this!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_19%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EUzziah%2C%20who%20was%20holding%20an%20incense%20burner%2C%20became%20furious.%20But%20as%20he%20was%20standing%20there%20raging%20at%20the%20priests%20before%20the%20incense%20altar%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple%2C%20leprosy%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E26%3A19%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Ea%20contagious%20skin%20disease.%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20Hebrew%20word%20used%20here%20and%20throughout%20this%20passage%20can%20describe%20various%20skin%20diseases.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20suddenly%20broke%20out%20on%20his%20forehead.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_20%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Azariah%20the%20high%20priest%20and%20all%20the%20other%20priests%20saw%20the%20leprosy%2C%20they%20rushed%20him%20out.%20And%20the%20king%20himself%20was%20eager%20to%20get%20out%20because%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20struck%20him.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_21%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20King%20Uzziah%20had%20leprosy%20until%20the%20day%20he%20died.%20He%20lived%20in%20isolation%20in%20a%20separate%20house%2C%20for%20he%20was%20excluded%20from%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20His%20son%20Jotham%20was%20put%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20royal%20palace%2C%20and%20he%20governed%20the%20people%20of%20the%20land.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_22%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20rest%20of%20the%20events%20of%20Uzziah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%2C%20from%20beginning%20to%20end%2C%20are%20recorded%20by%20the%20prophet%20Isaiah%20son%20of%20Amoz.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_26_23%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Uzziah%20died%2C%20he%20was%20buried%20with%20his%20ancestors%3B%20his%20grave%20was%20in%20a%20nearby%20burial%20field%20belonging%20to%20the%20kings%2C%20for%20the%20people%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BHe%20had%20leprosy.%26%23x201D%3B%20And%20his%20son%20Jotham%20became%20the%20next%20king.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_27_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJotham%20Rules%20in%20Judah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EJotham%20was%20twenty-five%20years%20old%20when%20he%20became%20king%2C%20and%20he%20reigned%20in%20Jerusalem%20sixteen%20years.%20His%20mother%20was%20Jerusha%2C%20the%20daughter%20of%20Zadok.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_27_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EJotham%20did%20what%20was%20pleasing%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sight.%20He%20did%20everything%20his%20father%2C%20Uzziah%2C%20had%20done%2C%20except%20that%20Jotham%20did%20not%20sin%20by%20entering%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20But%20the%20people%20continued%20in%20their%20corrupt%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_27_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EJotham%20rebuilt%20the%20upper%20gate%20of%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20He%20also%20did%20extensive%20rebuilding%20on%20the%20wall%20at%20the%20hill%20of%20Ophel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_27_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20built%20towns%20in%20the%20hill%20country%20of%20Judah%20and%20constructed%20fortresses%20and%20towers%20in%20the%20wooded%20areas.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_27_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EJotham%20went%20to%20war%20against%20the%20Ammonites%20and%20conquered%20them.%20Over%20the%20next%20three%20years%20he%20received%20from%20them%20an%20annual%20tribute%20of%207%2C500%20pounds%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E27%3A5a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3E100%26%23xA0%3Btalents%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B3%2C400%20kilograms%5D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20silver%2C%2050%2C000%20bushels%20of%20wheat%2C%20and%2050%2C000%20bushels%20of%20barley.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E27%3A5b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3E10%2C000%20cors%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B2%2C200%20kiloliters%5D%20%3Cem%3Eof%20wheat%2C%20and%2010%2C000%20cors%20of%20barley.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_27_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EKing%20Jotham%20became%20powerful%20because%20he%20was%20careful%20to%20live%20in%20obedience%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20his%20God.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_27_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20rest%20of%20the%20events%20of%20Jotham%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%2C%20including%20all%20his%20wars%20and%20other%20activities%2C%20are%20recorded%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Book%20of%20the%20Kings%20of%20Israel%20and%20Judah.%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_27_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20was%20twenty-five%20years%20old